    <h1>Coding Resources</h1>
    <p>
      Interested in tech but don't know where to start? Dipping your foot in the
      tech world can seem like a daunting task but it doesn't have to be! To
      make things easier for you, we've compiled a list of some free and paid
      resources to allow you to test the waters and see if a career in tech is
      the right fit for you. Check out the links below and get coding!
    </p>
    <!--Need to fix link for below - too long so I removed it-->
    <img scr=>
    <h2>Free Resources</h2>
    <p>
      Whether you're making a career change, coding for fun or deciding what
      career is right for you, the world of tech has a lot to offer. Rather than
      forking out hundreds or thousands on an expensive coding bootcamp or
      degree straight away, the below websites offer free courses in coding and
      development. This is a great way to see if coding is for you, without
      having to invest financially from the get-go.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a
        href="https://www.codecademy.com/?utm_source=pepperjam&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_term=229159&clickId=4066918519&pj_creativeid=2-438167&pj_publisherid=229159"
      >
        Codecademy
      </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Codecademy is one of the best-known free coding websites. Offering free
      resources in HTML, CSS, Javascript and more, it is a great option for
      beginners.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/"> freeCodeCamp </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Offering over 8,000+ tutorials covering topics in frontend and backend
      development, web design, python and more, freeCodecademy graduates have
      gone on to work for some of the biggest tech companies in the world.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.theodinproject.com/"> The Odin Project </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Founded on the belief that education should be free and accessible, the
      Odin Project offers free courses and tutorials for a variety of
      programming languages from basic html and CSS to ruby on rails and advice
      on getting hired. The Odin Project has a large open source community for
      all your programming queries.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.codeconquest.com/"> Code Conquest </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Designed specifically with newbie coders in mind, Code Conquest offers
      accessible coding resources with quizzes, tutorials and cheatsheets
      available for a wide range of coding languages. Best of all, it's all
      free!
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://code.org/"> Code.Org</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      With a view to increasing the number of kids learning computer programming
      as part of their k-12 education, Code.org offers a wide range of basic
      programming tutorials, created to be interactive and easily accessible.
      Don't let the fact this was designed for kids put you off, as the
      resources are available to beginners of all ages.
    </p>
    <h2>Paid Resources</h2>
    <p>
      If you already know the basics or are sure you want to invest in your
      programming journey, then check out the below resources and courses we've
      compiled of the most popular options.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.udemy.com/"> Udemy</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Udemy offers a wide range of coding courses, varying in length and price,
      so you can pick what best works for your skill level and goals.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.shecodes.io/"> SheCodes</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Designed specifically for women, SheCodes offers a range of flexible
      courses and a free intro course for potential learners to get a feel for
      the course style and structure. SheCodes courses can be taken full-time or
      part-time and students get a certificate upon completion.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/"> Coursera</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Similar to Udemy, Coursera offers a range of coding courses, varying in
      length and price so that you can choose the best option for your goals.
      Some courses offer certification and reviews are available on the site for
      all.
    </p>
    <h3>
      <a href="https://www.udacity.com/"> Udacity</a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Udacity also offers courses for those looking to pursue a career in the
      tech industry. Courses offered cover a wide range of tech careers from
      product management to AI programming, taught by industry experts through a
      flexible learning style curriculum.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
